## Continual-Bench v2
[[Continual-Bench v2]]
>>id: lp_lab00000005
>>type: dataset
>>what: 6-task class-incremental suite the lab evaluates every method on
>>location: nas://datasets/continual-bench-v2

## Eval Protocol v2
[[Eval Protocol v2]]
>>id: lp_lab00000006
>>type: protocol
>>what: 3 seeds · fixed task order · report mean forgetting + final accuracy
>>why: single-seed reports burned us in 2024 — variance swallowed the effect

## Replay prevents forgetting
[[Replay prevents forgetting]]
>>id: lp_lab00000007
>>type: hypothesis
>>claim: small-batch replay is sufficient to prevent catastrophic forgetting
>>status: revised — holds only below ~10k classes

## EXP-041 replay on Continual-Bench
[[EXP-041 replay on Continual-Bench]]
>>id: lp_lab00000008
>>type: experiment
>>ran: 2025-11
>>config: replay buffer 2%, 3 seeds

[[EXP-041 replay on Continual-Bench]] →(tests) [[Replay prevents forgetting]]
[[EXP-041 replay on Continual-Bench]] →(uses) [[Eval Protocol v2]]
[[EXP-041 replay on Continual-Bench]] →(uses) [[Continual-Bench v2]]
[[EXP-041 replay on Continual-Bench]] →(run-by) [[Sujin Park]]



## Result: replay holds at small scale
[[Result: replay holds at small scale]]
>>id: lp_lab00000009
>>type: result
>>finding: forgetting < 3% up to 1k classes
>>supports: [[Replay prevents forgetting]]

[[Result: replay holds at small scale]] →(derived-from) [[EXP-041 replay on Continual-Bench]]
[[Result: replay holds at small scale]] →(supports) [[Replay prevents forgetting]]

